Subject: My SSO login is not working after setup
Description: I went through the entire SSO activation process on my CybeArk IDP, but when I tried to test it, the page logged me out and I can no longer access the panel. My access user was enabled for failover, but the login page always takes me to my IDP, and after authenticating myself it displays this message: There has been an issue with your Single Sign On Process. Please check the Single Sign On Settings.
Solution_Comment__c: Solved using the instructions for SSO
